spanGrp.span: Should I say mine (name) in English?
Haap Hani_Guiga Haap Hani_Guiga hiigaire waanksana.
"Going after Daylight", "Going after daylight" they call me, I am here sitting.
Hainixjik eegi haastik hagihi hae_haakjene cii eejaxji.
In the morning, then, I picked blueberries near the house.
The Indians used to pick blueberries .
Ceekji ceekji heesgera hanaxgura, haaha waak hiacik haara
The first thing I heard, yes, my male (?) father
ceexji cexjihesgera hanxguna, ha'a, waakhianik haara
they call him (father) "All kinds of clouds" (Thunderclan).
Hiac haara hiya hiac hinuupra Heenara
One of my fathers brothers, the second one
hi'anc haara hiyaa (hiza) hiak hinubra heenana
zee ceekji waza haastik gihi gihiire <<ui>> eeja horakire horaksna.
he (father) told that they told that they used to picked blueberries.
ze'e ceexji waza haastik gihi gihire 'eja hoorkire horaksa
something missing between "gihire" and "'eja" -- LP: Yes, added <<ui>>.
Waaksik siireja heg waaksikra stoohiire nigesana hiiresunusguni.
The Indians used to live scattered in groups.
waaksik hiresa heg waakskra stoohire nigesanak (?) hiiresuunNsguni
Haastik gihiire waaksikra nigesana hoxatap eeja nige gihiire.
They used to pick blueberries here and there in the bush.
haastik gihre waakskra niigsana hoxatp 'eja niige gihiire
eesge (he)gu cii hociire haahao waipere cii hoci(ire) hesgesge hiiresununa.
zeesge niige (guu) cihociire aaho waipre cii ho(ci)
hesgesge = anaphora; used to refer to whatever was said before
"nige" really said? -- LP: No, deleted from tx and mo.
Naani eera eeja cii_hoijas hociire hegu zeegu stoo uire.
My mother (says) they used to live in groups together in the tent.
nanihera eja nanihera eja ciihoicas hociire heguze stol'uine
Eegi eegi haapregi hota hegu niheiza hegu nige howaraire haastik gihiire.
Some of them go in a group and go away picking berries.
'egi 'egi hapregi hot huniheza hegu niig howaraire haastink gihire
Hota cii eejasge waakrasge hegu eeja zeesge hiiresunu airena.
Some of the men stayed home, that's what they used to do; it was said.
hot ciiejasge waankrasge eja hegu zesge hiresunu aireen
"eja" and "hegu" other way round? -- LP: I think so, swapped on tx and mo.
That's the way they used to do it ... and there ...
'eegi 'eeja seem to belong to the following sentence and function as HESIT
Waak hiacik haara zeeja howajisge teenasge hegu waza wainasara uusguni.
That's where it came from, said the father, my father, he had TB
'egi waak hi'anjikhaara zeeja howaajisge 'eenasge hegu waza wanasra (mamanasara)) 'usguni
really "'egi" at the beginning? -- LP: Don't think so, removed on tx and mo.
Eeja jaaji eeja jaaji eera hakarani uunaak nii_haicep hakarani uunaak eeja nii_haicep huugirakiresunu.
They took care of him, my father, and he died (lost his breath), I heard that, that's what they used to tell me.
egi jaji esge eja jaji heera hakarani'unak eja niihaicep hakarani'unak eja niihaicep hugirak reesunu
beginning: "'eeja jaaji eeja jaaji 'ee-ra..."?; removed one "eja"; transcription doesn't seem to match spoken words from "niihaicep" -- LP: Changed beginning accordingly, not sure about the end.
Eegi zee zeegu hau huuwi hagoreiza hegu zeegu uusge (he)gu eegi Niis herege (he)gu eegi aasge haciwi.
And then we are coming to Wisconsin Dells and we lived close by.
'egi ze zegu ha'uhuwi hagoreiza hegu zeegu 'usg gu 'egi niiserege gu 'egi 'aasge haciwi
Naani eera hegu naani eera jaaji eera eesge hegu gooja
My mother and my dad over there
nani heera hegu naani heera jaji heere eesge hegu goj
haahaa jaagusge Necedah airegajasguni eeja heesge hagihi hahiwi.
we went picking to Necedah, I suppose.
aha'a jagusge Necedah airegaja sguni 'eja hesge hagihahiwi
Guha haap nuup haap taan (he)gu eesge hagiwi.
We arrived there in two or three days.
guha haaP haap nup tan gu eesge hagiw
switched "haap" and "nuup" -- LP: Yes, also switched on tx.
Heesge hakiriwi hegu hoxjanagi naani eera hagijite haasnaka eegi hoxjanaga nige peex hozu.
I helped mother to put berries in cans in the evening.
hege hagiwi hegu huxjanakgi naneera hakijite haasnkga egi huxcanakga niig peex hozu
Hegu haap nuup taani hauwi hogihi hiza hakini peex hozu zeegu hii.
We did that for two or three days, she filled over hundred bottles.
hegu haap nuupa taai ha 'uwin hogihisa (ha)kiin peex hozu jeegu hii
Eegi maani nee hiire. Hegu hegu tee hegu waruhoire zuura uu naaiire
During the winter they did this. They donate trying to make money.
egi maani nehire hegu hegu tee hegu waruxhoire zuura 'unane
Hegu jaaji eera waruho hii naani eera naac_hisgi.
My father went to donate (the berries), and mother scolded at him (probably because he gave away too much).
hegu jaji hera waruxohi nani hera naaciski
Ka eeja ka eeja (haa)ke peex waazuni waruhokje wagiuire.
I didn't can those jars for being donated.
ka 'eja ka 'eje ke peex waazuni waruhokje wagi'uine
ee nee hiyarucikjawi yaarege waau eegi eeja Jaaji eera eeja naac_hisgiiregaja.
My father was scolded, we could eat that, I thought.
ze nee hiaruucikkjnawi yaarge waa'u egi 'eja jaji heera eja naacisgire gaja
Hegu haawisunu hegu gipiesge hegu taakac hegu.
Thats the way we used to do it even when it was hot and it was a pleasant time.
hegu haawisunu hegu gipiesge hegu taakac hegu
Hegu raawaksge kiza nige hauwi zee hegu niisge zeegu haaptee.
We fought the mosquitos all over, that's the way it used to be and that's the way it is today.
hegu rawaksge kiisa niig ha'uwi ze hegu niisge zegu haapte'e
That's not the right thing, but I like it now.
kesgenigaja hegu zesge ze haipiini hegunige
(Haa)kesge (haa)kesge (he)gu haciijasge howatanaki hegu haassicga hagikje heesgani.
I don't know where to go to pick berries anymore.
keesge kasgegu (kesge) hajija-sge howataanagi hegu "Haasicga" hagiksesgani
ee uusge woorak hanira hiigirera hijahi hisekjanawi.
This is the end of the story, someone else should talk now.
